author: Rachael Levy
title: Here is Snapchat's roadshow schedule
text:
print 
Mike Nudelman/Business Insider 
Snapchat parent company Snap Inc. said in a filing Thursday that it was seeking an initial public offering valuation of up to $22 billion . 
It is looking to price its IPO on Wednesday, March 1, Business Insider has learned. 
The company said it is seeking to price shares between $14 and $16. 
Snap is looking to list 200 million shares on the New York Stock Exchange under the ticker "SNAP". 
The management team present will include CEO Evan Spiegel, chief strategy officer Imran Khan, and chief financial officer Andrew Vollero. 
The active bookrunners are Morgan Stanley, Goldman Sachs, JPMorgan, and Deutsche Bank. Passive bookrunners include Barclays, Credit Suisse, and Allen & Co. 
Here is the schedule for investors who plan to meet with the tech company. Friday, Feb 17: MidAtlantic Tuesday, Feb 21: New York Wednesday, Feb 22: New York Thursday, Feb 23: Boston Monday, Feb 27: Los Angeles / San Francisco Tuesday, Feb 28: San Francisco Wednesday, March 1: New York pricing
